				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have to tell you that I'm STILL confused.  HO is <span style="font-style: italic">very</span> unintuitive.
<br />

<br />
I see this circle come up with unfamiliar icons that don't at all match what I'm used to seeing in my hotbars.  If the hotbar icons weren't blinking I'd have no clue what to do.  With several of them blinking I can't figure out which is best to press.  And the wheel icons blink too.  Am I supposed to press them?  And then the hotbar icon that is blinking?
<br />

<br />
Then I see a different circle come up with different icons.  And then hotbar buttons blink or don't blink.  
<br />

<br />
I'm a fighter.  I see a blue horn come up and the first thing I think is: I'm no bard, that's not for me.  Well, it's blue, so it <span style="font-style: italic">is</span> me, but what the heck do I do with it?
<br />

<br />
When I see this page come up on your site, I don't understand it at all: <a href="http://gnorrath.com/fighterHO.htm." target="_blank">http://gnorrath.com/fighterHO.htm.</a>  What do the Y, N and ? mean to me?  In solo, why is the Sword to the right of the Shield?  Does it mean I will see a sword related hot bar icon blink first then a shield icon blink?  Why is the Horn all the way to the right past the Y?  In Group, what are Slots?  Is the fact that Fighter is all the way to the left mean that if a symbol is shown for me mean I'm always first?  Why are there 4 - (dashes) in many of the horizontal lines?  AARGH!!
<br />

<br />
I see no results from pushing buttons.  I can't tell, ever, if the HO worked or not.  Have to ask groupmates.  How they can tell I have no clue.
<br />

<br />
In the HO tips thread, it says, KNOW YOUR ICONS.  Ok, how do I cross reference the HO wheel icons to the ones in my hotbars?  Or do I?
<br />

<br />
I guess after looking over your site, I still feel I'm missing something VERY basic that would make HO intelligible to me.  I don't even know what questions to ask.  I bet the ones I did ask here are silly, but I have to tell you, I'm really not getting it.  
<br />

<br />
And I'm a smart guy, usually.  NOT trying to be critical of the work you've done.  Just trying to understand.
<br />

<br />
And, I can tell you I'm frustrated because I want and need to know now.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
