				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First, thanks for the feedback <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" /> We're trying to change things to make it more understandable. I'm currently trying to re-label the tables to have more descriptive titles. 
<br />

<br />
Right click on your icons in your hotbar. Then click on examine. You will see two icons. One is the icon for the skill/spell, it's the same one you see in your hotbar. The second is the HO icon that it is linked to. 
<br />

<br />
The horn in your question is taunt. Also the boot is kick, the sword is wild blow. 
<br />

<br />
In the chart, the icons listed on the left side are the starter chain. They have to be done in that order to start a heroic opportunity. The icons on the right side are what will appear in the HO wheel. Such as the horn in your question. That is the skill that will actually complete the HO.
<br />

<br />
The fighter tutorial should be up tonight, I'll link it so hopefully you'll have a better idea of how to use HO's. 
<br />

<br />
Thanks again
<br />
Kresken</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
