			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Kresken, thanks a lot for the input.
<br />

<br />
Speaking only for myself, the thing you said that was "magical" was this statement: "Right click on your icons in your hotbar. Then click on examine. You will see two icons. One is the icon for the skill/spell, it's the same one you see in your hotbar. The second is the HO icon that it is linked to."
<br />

<br />
Suddenly, the link between the two systems began to be clearer, to me.
<br />

<br />
I'd suggest telling people a few basic things now that I have solo HO figured out.
<br />

<br />
1.  Every character gets a HO hot bar icon.  Learn which your's is.  (List them for the reader.)
<br />

<br />
2.  Right click on your icons in your hotbar. Then click on Examine. You will see two icons. One is the icon for the skill/spell, it's the same one you see in your hotbar. The second is the HO icon that it is linked to.
<br />

<br />
3.  Start right away in solo encounters trying to learn how to use HOs.  Don't wait.
<br />

<br />
4.  There are two ways to fight a solo encounter.  The one most people start with is just using hot bar icons.  The second is: use the HO button for your class in nearly every opportunity you have and then one or more of the blinking hot bar icons.  Sometimes, I've found you can use the HO button up to 3 or 4 times in one solo encounter.
<br />

<br />
Question on group HO play: my guild does not have the group HO thing quite figured out yet.  For us, we often have two characters of the same class in a group.  In this case, when the HO ring comes up, two people could click on the linked hot bar icon.  Thus, (I think) we often have a failure since we haven't assigned "lead" players to be responsible for HO.  Do you recommend assigning "lead" HO icon clickers when a group has two or more of the same class?  Or am I still misunderstanding group play?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
